data.description: BREATH TAKING VIEWS.  Deep Water with 24' Boat Dock.  A true one of a kind for sure.  Owner says countless people have stopped to tell them this is their favorite house in the county.  Coming to market November 15th with a new standing seam metal roof.  Separate apartment on ground level is currently an Airbnb generating 30K + a year.   This is a boater, fisherman, kayaking, nature watching, star gazers paradise.  Take in the sunsets and the big dipper over the water, marshes and creeks.  The Lockwood Folly is home to many species of birds and are seen regularly from this property to include Bald Eagle, Wood Stork, Roseate Spoonbill,  Snowy Egret, Blue Heron, Pelican, Painted Bunting, Marsh Hen, King Fisher and many more.  Otters, Rays, Dolphins feed on the bait are among the habitat.  Some of the best fishing, oystering, clamming and mussels are found right out the backdoor.  Just a short half a mile paddle in the kayak or by boat to Oak Island and its beaches.  Many restaurants less than 2 miles from the dock.  Great for jumping out for dinner and sunset on your boat.  The neighborhood is a quiet fishing village and golf cart community.  Many community events for the young and old.  Home to the annual golf cart parade, some of the best fireworks and 4th of July activities around.  No city taxes, no HOA, saves on the monthly expenses and restrictions.The main home is a 3 bedroom 2 bath and there is an efficiency studio apartment with one bath.  This charming coastal Nantucket style home has been redone and there are so many new features there just too many to mention.  New HVAC, cedar siding, window/doors, stamped concrete drive & golf cart path, kitchen to include custom cabinets, granite counters & back splash, Zline gas range, refinished pickled heart pine floor, bar/lounge w/cypress walls, picket fence, refinished heart pine pickled floors,  sod & irrigation, pavered patio, tiled lanai, , and much more.  Prof photos coming soon.  An absolute must
